column1: RemarkThe well was drilled as a stratigraphic test with the primary objective being investigation of the hydrocarbon content of Lower Cretaceous to Triassic sedimentary rocks.The Upper and Lower Jurassic and Middle-Upper Triassic sections penetrated good reservoir sandstones with Cretaceous and Lower Triassic shale sections providing top and bottom seals to these potential reservoir beds. No indications of oil were detected and no fluorescence or cut were noted in the cuttings. Numerous gas shows were noted from 442-1052m, in the Upper Cretaceous Bathurst Island Shales.Plover 1 is located in the Bonaparte Gulf-Timor Sea area, 191 km WSW of Gull 1 and 132 km SE of Osprey 1.
